entry.name: Panorama of ancient metazoan macromolecular complexes: Mus musculus
entry.description: By combining extensive biochemical fractionation with quantitative mass spectrometry, we directly examined the composition of soluble multiprotein complexes among diverse animal models. The project has been jointly supervised by Andrew Emili and Edward M. Marcotte. Project website: http://metazoa.med.utoronto.ca

additional_fields.field: Brachyury-GFP tagged mouse embryonic stem cells were obtained from Peter Zandstra (University of Toronto). ES cells were maintained in DMEM/F12 and Neurobasal buffer (Invitrogen) supplemented with N2-Supplement, B27 + RA, 10% bovine serum albumin (BSA), Glutamax, penicillin, streptomycin, 1.5 × 10−4 M monothioglycerol (MTG, Sigma) and LIF (1%) and BMP4 (10 ng/mL). ES cells were cultured on gelatin coated tissue culture polystyrene and dissociated with TrypLE (Invitrogen). Cells were harvested using 10% fetal bovine serum (FBS) in DMEM and centrifuged at 900g for 5 min. The cell pellet was washed with IMDM and centrifuged at 900g, then re-suspended and lysed with the same protocol as for human cells, using a protocol adapted from previous publication (Havugimana et al., Cell, 2002). The lysates then were subjected to ion exchange fractionation using an Agilent 1100 HPLC system.Proteins from the HPLC fractions were precipitated, resuspended and digested in solution with trypsin, dried and re-solubilised before being analyzed by LC-MS/MS using a nanoflow HPLC System (EASY-nLC; Proxeon) coupled to LTQ Orbitrap Velos (Thermo Fisher).

FASTA file was downloaded as described in the manuscript and processed to retain only the longest sequence for each gene, to simplify orthology mapping between species, as the project was focused on conserved complexes. Samples were searched using 3 search engines: Tide, INSPECT, and MSGFDB and combined to create quantification using MSblender (Kwon, Choi et. al. J. Proteome Research 2011). Tide search output is provided in a form processed for best hits with MSblender; MSGFDB and INSPECT search output is provided directly, when available.
